report_text: left-sided aicd device is noted with single lead terminating in the right ventricle . heart size is normal . mediastinal and hilar contours are unremarkable . pulmonary vasculature is not engorged . patchy opacities are noted in the lung bases likely reflective of atelectasis . no focal consolidation pleural effusion or pneumothorax is present . there are no acute osseous abnormalities .
